# ADK Orchestrator - Directory Structure

This document explains the directory structure of the ADK orchestrator backend for BYO Judge.

## Overview

The ADK orchestrator follows a clean architecture pattern with separation between agent logic, shared utilities, evaluation framework, and testing infrastructure. The structure enforces ASCII-only Python code for optimal ADK performance.

## Root Structure

```
back/grant-prototype/            # Pythong V1 Protoytpe(In development)
├── .outputs/                    # Folder for outputs from agent
│   ├── grant                    # Output from g## commands, agents or skills
│   ├── company                  # Output from c## commands, agents or skills
│   ├── matching                 # Output from m## commands, agents or skills
│   └── application              # Output from a## commands, agents or skills
│   └── signoff                  # Output from s## commands, agents or skills
├── scrapers/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── base_scraper.py
